                    <history>
                        <origin notBefore="1225" notAfter="1250" cert="high" evidence="conjecture">
                            <p>Written in <origPlace>Iceland</origPlace> in <origDate
                                    notBefore="1225" notAfter="1250" cert="high"
                                    evidence="conjecture">the second quarter of the thirteenth
                                    century</origDate> (<bibl>
                                    <ref type="secondary" target="Lindblad1952">Lindblad 1952</ref>,
                                    p. 92</bibl>). <name type="person" key="KriKaa001"
                                >Kålund</name>'s dating: The first half of the thirteenth century, (<bibl>
                                    <ref type="secondary-1" target="KKKat">Katalog</ref>
                                    <biblScope unit="volume">II</biblScope>
                                    <biblScope unit="page">58</biblScope></bibl>).</p>
                        </origin>
                        <provenance>
                            <p>Previously the leaf was put inside a cover on which <name
                                    type="person" key="ArnMag001">Árni Magnússon</name> wrote: <q
                                    xml:lang="is">Þetta fragmentum fan<expan>n</expan> eg anno
                                        <date>1725</date>. in<expan>n</expan>ani
                                        hryggnu<expan>m</expan> ä Iislendsku kvere, er ätt hafde Sr
                                        Þord<expan>ur</expan> Jonsson i Hitardal, <expan>og</expan>
                                    epter han<expan>n</expan> Þorsteinn Þordarson. Kvered var
                                        in<expan>n</expan>saumadad forlage Þ<expan>or</expan>steins
                                    Þordarsonar, þvi in<expan>n</expan>ani bandinu voru .2.
                                    sendibref til Þorsteins dat. 1673. <expan>og</expan> 76] anno
                                        <date>1676</date>. eda sidar. feck eg þ<expan>ad</expan> af
                                        <name type="person" key="GudTho006">Gudmunde
                                        Þorleifssyne</name> ä Eyre, en<expan>n</expan>
                                        h<expan>an</expan>n hafde feinged þ<expan>ad</expan> ä
                                    Skarde, ad eg þykizt vist vita</q>. In his catalogue (<bibl><ref
                                        target="KKKat">Katalog</ref><biblScope unit="volume"
                                        >II</biblScope><biblScope unit="page"
                                >58</biblScope></bibl>), Kålund, however, doubted that the cover
                                originally belonged to this fragment.</p>
                        </provenance>
                        <acquisition>
                            <p>Assuming that the text on the previous cover is concerning this leaf 
                                <name type="person" key="ArnMag001">Árni Magnússon</name> got it
                                from <name type="person" key="GudTho006">Guðmundur
                                    Þorleifsson</name>.</p>
                        </acquisition>
